Gait analysis is crucial for timely diagnosis and treatment, often relying on costly optical motion capture systems. Recent breakthroughs in computer vision and deep learning have enabled the development of more accessible and affordable alternatives. This study introduces a novel spatio-temporal transformer network to determine essential gait metrics from videos captured using a single camera. Experimental findings on a publicly available dataset of cerebral palsy patients demonstrate that the proposed approach outperforms existing methods, accurately predicting gait parameters such as walking speed, deviation index, and knee angle, with fewer parameters and automated feature extraction.
